#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/js-request-idle-callback.md
M|rules|title: Defer Non-Critical Work with requestIdleCallback
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: keeps UI responsive during background tasks
M|rules|tags: javascript, performance, idle, scheduling, anl
M|rules|**Impact: MEDIUM (keeps UI responsive during background tasks)**
M|rules|Use `requestIdleCallback()` to schedule non-critical work during browser idle periods. This keeps the main thread free for user interactions and animations, reducing jank and improving perceived perfo
M|rules|**Incorrect (blocks main thread during user interaction):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|function handleSearch(query: string) {
M|rules|const results = searchItems(query)
M|rules|setResults(results)
M|rules|// These block the main thread immediately
M|rules|anl.track('search', { query })
M|rules|saveToRecentSearches(query)
M|rules|prefetchTopResults(results.slice(0, 3))
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (defers non-critical work to idle time):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|function handleSearch(query: string) {
M|rules|const results = searchItems(query)
M|rules|setResults(results)
M|rules|// Defer non-critical work to idle periods
M|rules|requestIdleCallback(() => {
M|rules|anl.track('search', { query })
M|rules|})
M|rules|requestIdleCallback(() => {
M|rules|saveToRecentSearches(query)
M|rules|})
M|rules|requestIdleCallback(() => {
M|rules|prefetchTopResults(results.slice(0, 3))
M|rules|})
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**With timeout for required work:**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|// Ensure anl fires within 2 seconds even if browser stays busy
M|rules|requestIdleCallback(
M|rules|() => anl.track('page_view', { path: location.pathname }),
M|rules|{ timeout: 2000 }
M|rules|)
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Chunking large tasks:**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|function processLargeDataset(items: Item[]) {
M|rules|let index = 0
M|rules|function processChunk(deadline: IdleDeadline) {
M|rules|// Process items while we have idle time (aim for <50ms chunks)
M|rules|while (index < items.length && deadline.timeRemaining() > 0) {
M|rules|processItem(items[index])
M|rules|index++
M|rules|}
M|rules|// Schedule next chunk if more items remain
M|rules|if (index < items.length) {
M|rules|requestIdleCallback(processChunk)
M|rules|}
M|rules|}
M|rules|requestIdleCallback(processChunk)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**With fallback for unsupported browsers:**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const scheduleIdleWork = window.requestIdleCallback ?? ((cb: () => void) => setTimeout(cb, 1))
M|rules|scheduleIdleWork(() => {
M|rules|// Non-critical work
M|rules|})
M|rules|```
M|rules|**When to use:**
M|rules|- anl and telemetry
M|rules|- Saving state to localStorage/IndexedDB
M|rules|- Prefetching resources for likely next actions
M|rules|- Processing non-urgent data transformations
M|rules|- Lazy initialization of non-critical features
M|rules|**When NOT to use:**
M|rules|- User-initiated actions that need immediate feedback
M|rules|- Rendering updates the user is waiting for
M|rules|- Time-sensitive operations